cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.DL 

This paper deals with lower bounds on dynamic data structures and graph problems, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves graph algorithms and pattern matching, which fall under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), respectively. Finally, the paper introduces new techniques for obtaining amortized lower bounds, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
